## Stack: React Native 0.76+ + Expo SDK 52+

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| Runtime | React Native 0.76+ â€” New Architecture (Fabric + TurboModules + JSI) is the default. Old Architecture is removed in 0.82+. |
| JS engine | Hermes (Hermes V1 is the default in 0.84+) |
| Toolchain | Expo SDK 52+ (managed workflow) |
| Routing | Expo Router v4 (file-based, `app/` directory) |
| Language | TypeScript strict mode |
| Server state | TanStack Query v5 |
| Forms / validation | TanStack Form v6 + Zod |
| Styling | NativeWind v4 (Tailwind for RN) |
| Animations | Reanimated 3 (worklets on the UI thread) |
| Lists | FlashList (not FlatList) |
| Unit tests | Jest + React Native Testing Library |
| E2E | Maestro (YAML flows) |
| Releases | EAS Build + EAS Submit |

### Conventions

- **New Architecture is mandatory.** Do NOT opt out via `newArchEnabled: false`. Do NOT mix legacy Native Modules with TurboModules in the same project.
- **File-based routing in `app/`.** Lowercase, hyphen-separated route filenames (`user-settings.tsx`). The `app/` tree is for route files only â€” put business logic in `features/`, `lib/`, `hooks/`, etc.
- **NativeWind for styling.** Do NOT mix `className` (NativeWind) and `StyleSheet.create` in the same component. Pick one per file; default to NativeWind.
- **Animate with Reanimated 3 worklets.** Do NOT use the legacy `Animated` API. Use `useSharedValue` for animation state, `useAnimatedStyle` for derived styles, `runOnJS` to call back into JS land.
- **TanStack Query for server state.** Do NOT call `fetch` inside `useEffect` for data loading. Define query keys via factory pattern; set sane `staleTime` / `gcTime` defaults at the `QueryClient` level.
- **Never block the JS thread.** Heavy work goes into a Reanimated worklet, a background task, or off-device. Profile with Hermes / Chrome DevTools when a screen feels janky.
- **Verify on both platforms.** Before declaring done, run the change on an iOS simulator AND an Android emulator. Platform-specific bugs are common.
- **Check New-Arch compatibility before adding native deps.** Run `npx react-native-new-arch-check` after `expo install <pkg>`. Outdated libs fail at runtime, not build time.

### Common commands

```bash
npx expo start                       # local dev (Metro + Expo Go / dev client)
npx expo start --ios                 # boot iOS simulator
npx expo start --android             # boot Android emulator
npx expo install <pkg>               # add a dep at the SDK-compatible version
npx react-native-new-arch-check      # confirm deps support the New Architecture
npm run lint                         # eslint
npm test                             # jest + RNTL unit / component tests
npx maestro test .maestro/           # run Maestro E2E flows
eas build --platform ios             # cloud build via EAS
eas build --platform android         # cloud build via EAS
eas submit --platform ios            # submit to App Store (asks for confirmation)
```

